Since this is just a report, no action is required.

FreeBSD 12.x cannot build 1.76.0.
The bootstrap binary specified by ports cannot be run for the following reasons

ld-elf.so.1: /lib/libc.so.7: version FBSD_1.7 required by /wrkdirs/usr/ports/lang/rust/work/bootstrap/bin/cargo not found

If the bootstrap is made to use one previous version, the build will stop for the following reasons

Unexpected rustc version: 1.74.0, we should use 1.75.x/1.76.0 to build source with 1.76.0

With the following fix, 12.4-STABLE has successfully built 1.76.0.
I don't know what negative impact this change will have :)

--- a/lib/libc/Versions.def
+++ b/lib/libc/Versions.def
@@ -43,3 +43,6 @@ FBSD_1.6 {
 # Please do NOT increment the version of this namespace.
 FBSDprivate_1.0 {
 } FBSD_1.6;
+
+FBSD_1.7 {
+} FBSD_1.6;
